
[1]enthusiast

   ENTHU'SIAST, n. enthu'ziast.

   1. One who imagines he has special or supernatural converse with God,
   or special communications from him.

   2. One whose imagination is warmed; one whose mind is highly excited
   with the love or in the pursuit of an object; a person of ardent zeal;
   as an enthusiast in poetry or music.

   3. One of elevated fancy or exalted ideas.
